            <thetext>With the 3.0 release, we introduced the new contrib 2.0 catalogue which, until now, did not have much success. One reason for that could be the way of adding contribs to the catalogue which requires a calculated hash value for the contrib artifact. This is a tedious process, especially if contrib developers want to have a continuos delivery. Therefore, we should think of removing this hash requirement even event if it would mean that the automatic contrib download would be removed as well.</thetext>
